{{for|the airline|Air One}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox Magazine | title = Airone | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | frequency = [[wikt:Monthly|Monthly]] | circulation = | category = [[List of science magazines|Science]] | company = [[Cairo Communication]] | founded = {{start date and age|1981}} | country = Italy | based = Milan, Italy | language = Italian | website = [http://www.cairoeditore.it/Airone/ ''Airone''] | issn = }}
'''''Airone''''' ({{lang-en|[[Heron]]}}) is an Italian [[List of science magazines|science magazine]] devoted to science and technology issues. It is published in [[Milan]], Italy, by Editoriale Giorgio Mondadori (former company, now a division of Cairo Editore, a subsidiary of [[Cairo Communication]]).
==History and profile== ''Airone'' was founded in 1981 as an ecologist magazine primarily containing articles about animal world, nature, ethnology and geography.<ref>{{cite news|title=La natura firmata Airone in una collana "video"|issue=286|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|date=8 November 1988|page=15}}</ref><ref name="l'un">{{cite news|last1=Antonio Del Giudice|title=Airone a dieci anni parte per l'Urss|newspaper=[[L'Unità]]|date=14 May 1991|page=18}}</ref> The founder and first director was Egidio Gavazzi.<ref name="l'un"/> It was for years the most widely circulated scientific magazine in Italy,<ref name=PrimaOnline>{{cite news|title=Periodici – ‘Airone’. Prova ancora a volare alto|url=http://www.primaonline.it/2008/12/17/62295/periodici-airone-prova-ancora-a-volare-alto/|accessdate=19 August 2014|publisher=PrimaOnline|date=17 December 2008}}</ref><ref>''[[La Civiltà Cattolica]]''. Collection Issues 3378-3383. Society of Jesus, 1991.</ref> with a peak of average circulation of about 250,000 copies per month.<ref name="PrimaOnline"/><ref>{{cite book|author=Marco Gisotti, Tessa Gelisio|title=Guida ai Green Jobs: Come l'ambiente sta cambiando il mondo del lavoro|publisher=Edizioni Ambiente, 2012|isbn=8866270377}}</ref> Between 1985 and 1986 it co-produced with [[RAI]] the [[nature documentary]] series ''Pan''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Laura Putti|title=Pan: arriva la trasmissione dalla parte degli animali|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1985/11/26/pan-arriva-la-trasmissione-dalla-parte-degli.html?ref=search|accessdate=19 August 2014|newspaper=[[La Repubblica]]|date=26 November 1985|page=31}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Laura Putti|title=Pan, piu ricco tutto nuovo|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1986/10/26/pan-piu-ricco-tutto-nuovo.html?ref=search|newspaper=La Repubblica|accessdate=19 August 2014|date=26 October 1986|page=25}}</ref> In 1989 it was launched a spin-off for the younger readers, ''Airone Junior'', renamed ''Dodo'' in April 1995.<ref name=nssh>{{cite book|author=Gianni Bono|title=Guida al fumetto italiano|publisher=Epierre, 2003|pages=32–33}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Silvia Maoli|title=Ecco Airone junior. Una nuova rivista ai baby-ecologisti|date=8 November 1989|issue=298|newspaper=[[La Stampa|Stampa Sera]]|page=2}}</ref>
''Airone'' was described as a "magazine similar to ''[[National Geographic (magazine)|National Geographic]]'', but perhaps more conservation-minded",<ref>{{cite book|author=James Lasdun, Pia Davis|title=Tuscany and Umbria|publisher=Penguin, 2004|isbn=1440651108}}</ref> and it was referred to as "a stunning natural history magazine, the best of several European magazines".<ref>{{cite book|author=William A. Katz, Linda Sternberg Katz|title=Magazines for Libraries - Ninth Edition|publisher=R. R. Bowker, 1997|isbn=0835239071}}</ref> In an article about the first ten years of the magazine, the ''[[L'Unità]]'' journalist Antonio Del Giudice pointed how the magazine was "not just an editorial phenomenon, but also a cultural, political e social phenomenon".<ref name="l'un"/>
The circulation of ''Airone'' was 94,000 copies in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author=Anne Austin et. al. |title=Western Europe Market and Media Fact |url=http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact_2008/Western%20Europe%20Market%20&%20MediaFact%202008.pdf |work=Zenith Optimedia |accessdate=10 April 2015 |date=2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205131709/http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact_2008/Western%20Europe%20Market%20%26%20MediaFact%202008.pdf |archivedate=5 February 2015 }}</ref> In December 2013 the magazine had a circulation of 83,000 copies per month.<ref>{{cite news|title=Diffusione Stampa - Dati mensili Mensili 12-2013|url=http://www.primaonline.it/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Ads-mensili-dicembre1.xls|accessdate=19 August 2014|work=PrimaOnline|date=March 2014}}</ref>
