'''Amandus Heinrich Christian Zietz''' (1839–1921) was a zoologist born in [[Hamburg]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]], and best known for his work at the [[South Australian Museum]].<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=A-JCByVyQH0C |author=Brian Saunders |title=Discovery of Australia's Fishes: A History of Australian Ichthyology to 1930 |chapter=Waite |pages=290–316 |year=2012}}</ref><ref name=NLA>[http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/208456922?q=Amandus+Heinrich+Christian+Zietz&c=picture&versionId=228749281 1890 photograph, National Library of Australia collection]</ref> His son [[Frederick Robert Zietz]] was also a zoologist.<ref name=NLA/>

