{{Taxobox | name = ''Enterovirus D'' | virus_group = iv | ordo = ''[[Picornavirales]]'' | familia = ''[[Picornaviridae]]'' | genus = ''[[Enterovirus]]'' | species = ''Enterovirus D'' | subdivision_ranks = Subtypes | subdivision = [[Enterovirus 68]], [[Enterovirus 70]], [[Enterovirus 94]], [[Enterovirus 111]], [[Enterovirus 120]] }}
'''Enterovirus D''' is a species of [[enterovirus]] which causes disease in humans. Five subtypes have been identified to date:
*[[Enterovirus 68]]: causes respiratory disease, and is associated with [[acute flaccid paralysis]] (AFP) – a disease similar to [[polio]]. *[[Enterovirus 70]]: causes outbreaks of acute hemorrhagic [[conjunctivitis]]. *[[Enterovirus 94]]: has been associated with a single case of AFP. *[[Enterovirus 111]]: has been associated with a single case of AFP, and has been found in [[primate]] feces. *[[Enterovirus 120]]: has only been found in non-human primate feces.
