{{Infobox non-profit | Non-profit_name = Institute of Political Studies | Non-profit_logo = ИПС.jpg | logo_size = 150px | Non-profit_type = | founded_date = 1968 | founder = Republic of Serbia | location = [[Belgrade]], [[Republic of Serbia]] | origins = Faculty of Political Science - Belgrade | key_people = Živojin Đurić, director }}
'''Institute of Political Studies in Belgrade''' is an academic [[institution]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]]. It is for research of [[political science]].
== History == The institute was started in 1968. It developed out of the research unit of the High School of Political Science. It developed into an independent scientific institution. After separating from the Faculty of Political Science in Belgrade,<ref name="fpn">{{cite web|url=http://www.fpn.bg.ac.rs/en/ |title=Faculty of Political Sciences - University of Belgrade|website=fpn.bg.ac.rs|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="bg">{{cite web|url=http://www.bg.ac.rs/eng/memb/facult/soc-hum/en_fpn.php |title=see|website=bg.ac.rs|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref> the Institute for Political Studies was given the status of independent scientific institution.
== Journals == The current periodical editions of the Institute are:<ref name="ipsbgd">{{cite web|url=http://www.ipsbgd.edu.rs/serbian_political_thought.html |title=Институт за политичке студије|website=ipsbgd.edu.rs|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref> *''Serbian Political Thought '' *''Political Review'' *''National Interest''
